Aviva to Appoint McFarlane as Chairman, Sunday Telegraph Says

-- B y   E m m a   C h a r l t o n
-- 
2011-06-05T11:16:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-05/aviva-to-appoint-mcfarlane-as-chairman-sunday-telegraph-says.html
Aviva Plc (AV/) , the U.K.’s second-biggest
insurer by market value, will appoint John McFarlane as chairman
to replace Colin Sharman, the Sunday Telegraph  reported , without
saying where it got the information.  McFarlane has been approved by Aviva’s board and
appointments committee, according to the  newspaper . His name has
been passed on to the U.K. Financial Services Authority for
regulatory approval, which can take a number of weeks, the
Sunday Telegraph said.  Andrew Reid, a spokesman for the company, declined to
comment by mobile phone today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emma Charlton in London at 
